It's okay, ma'am. I'm a cop.

48
00:04:18,880 --> 00:04:19,961
Thank you, officer.

49
00:04:24,520 --> 00:04:25,687
Excuse me, ma'am!

50
00:04:26,883 --> 00:04:27,951
Miss!

51
00:04:28,102 --> 00:04:32,465
- I don't know some diapers or some...
- Excuse me, miss. You dropped this.

52
00:04:44,160 --> 00:04:45,957
Somebody call 9-1-1!

53
00:04:46,023 --> 00:04:47,040
Oh my God!

54
00:04:47,190 --> 00:04:48,258
Are you okay?

55
00:04:48,640 --> 00:04:49,694
My car!

56
00:04:50,516 --> 00:04:51,574
My car!

57
00:05:06,788 --> 00:05:11,069
Mr. Hopper, your dog
bark very hard last night.

58
00:05:11,324 --> 00:05:13,550
Oh, sorry about that, Mr. Zeitoun.

59
00:05:16,290 --> 00:05:18,445
You have a leak from upstairs.

60
00:05:18,740 --> 00:05:20,515
My wife say plumbers come.

61
00:05:20,629 --> 00:05:21,973
- Now we have leak.
- Okay.

62
00:05:22,049 --> 00:05:23,970
- Thank you.
- You have leak. We have leak.

63
00:05:35,925 --> 00:05:36,983
Rambis?

64
00:05:40,140 --> 00:05:41,183
Rambis.

65
00:05:59,220 --> 00:06:02,492
Rambis. Psycho dog,
did you make this mess?

66
00:06:11,365 --> 00:06:14,000
All right, all right, I get it.
Give me this.

67
00:06:16,072 --> 00:06:17,620
<i>You have nine messages.</i>

68
00:06:18,630 --> 00:06:19,868
<i>Message one.</i>

69
00:06:20,877 --> 00:06:22,049
<i>Message two.</i>

70
00:06:29,680 --> 00:06:30,697
Hello.

71
00:06:30,876 --> 00:06:33,414
Sis, I got six hang ups from you
last night. What's goin' on?

72
00:06:33,922 --> 00:06:36,080
Nothing. We just... We just had a little

73
00:06:36,256 --> 00:06:38,730
problem with the phone.
But it's okay now.

74
00:06:38,968 --> 00:06:40,460
<i>You sure?</i>
You sound kinda rattled?

75
00:06:42,019 --> 00:06:43,710
<i>It's... we're just late for school.</i>

76
00:06:43,758 --> 00:06:46,046
So we'll talk later, okay? Bye.

77
00:06:54,687 --> 00:06:56,380
<i>Message seven.</i>

78
00:06:57,480 --> 00:06:59,731
<i>Damn it, where you at?
It's me, Damien.</i>

79
00:06:59,864 --> 00:07:02,540
<i>Turn on your cell phone.
They hit the safe house, Hop.</i>

80
00:07:02,874 --> 00:07:04,500
<i>You need to come get my ass.</i>

81
00:07:05,060 --> 00:07:06,620
Police! Hands up!

82
00:07:06,800 --> 00:07:08,387
Easy! I'm a cop. I'm a cop!

83
00:07:10,800 --> 00:07:13,300
Okay, okay, I'm relaxed.

84
00:07:13,825 --> 00:07:16,810
- Detective Brett Hopper?
- Yeah. Get these guys off of me.

85
00:07:16,877 --> 00:07:19,058
You're under arrest
for the murder of assistant D.A.

86
00:07:19,097 --> 00:07:19,924
Alberto Garza.

87
00:07:19,971 --> 00:07:22,190
- What?
- You have the right to remain silent.

88
00:07:22,304 --> 00:07:24,870
If you give up the right
to remain silent, anything you say...

89
00:07:38,100 --> 00:07:40,030
- Have a seat.
- Before you all apologize

90
00:07:40,124 --> 00:07:41,551
for breaking down my door,

91
00:07:41,911 --> 00:07:43,064
I want to see the warrant.

92
00:07:43,196 --> 00:07:46,055
'Cause you had to have more
than some lame-ass anonymous tip

93
00:07:46,140 --> 00:07:48,859
to get a judge to sign off
on that kind of a blitz.

94
00:07:48,940 --> 00:07:50,849
Well, they told us you'd puff up.

95
00:07:51,180 --> 00:07:52,371
I'm detective Choi.

96
00:07:52,790 --> 00:07:53,989
Detective Spivak.

97
00:07:54,075 --> 00:07:55,195
I've had the pleasure.

98
00:07:55,261 --> 00:07:59,078
Look, you know what we do in here,
all the tactics, the back and forth,

99
00:07:59,190 --> 00:08:00,954
so I'm coming straight at you.

100
00:08:02,480 --> 00:08:04,357
What did you have against Garza?

101
00:08:06,370 --> 00:08:07,750
You gotta be kidding, right?

102
00:08:07,882 --> 00:08:11,020
We've got the murder weapon
with your prints on it.

103
00:08:13,090 --> 00:08:15,493
All right, well,
a gun's easy enough to plant.

104
00:08:15,682 --> 00:08:18,203
Prints are doable, too,
a little tougher. Where'd you get it?

105
00:08:18,241 --> 00:08:19,710
Where do you think we got it?

106
00:08:19,783 --> 00:08:23,086
I don't know, but chances are,
whoever gave you the gun is in on it.

107
00:08:23,161 --> 00:08:25,350
- Now tell me where you got it.
- Your place.

108
00:08:25,483 --> 00:08:26,532
Your closet.

109
00:08:26,880 --> 00:08:27,928
The closet?

110
00:08:31,060 --> 00:08:32,530
Pretty stupid move, man.

111
00:08:33,000 --> 00:08:35,232
Why would you hang on
to something like that?

112
00:08:35,582 --> 00:08:37,985
Somebody broke into my place
and put that gun there.

113
00:08:38,051 --> 00:08:40,251
Now the neighbor said something
about a plumber,

114
00:08:40,336 --> 00:08:43,209
- and my dog was going crazy, so...
- Why'd you do it, Hopper?

115
00:08:43,276 --> 00:08:45,883
Was it personal, or did Garza
have something on you?

116
00:08:46,035 --> 00:08:47,570
All right, you guys aren't.

117
00:08:49,670 --> 00:08:53,130
According to the newspapers, Garza
was hit sometime last night, right?

118
00:08:53,252 --> 00:08:54,668
I was with somebody last night.

119
00:08:54,791 --> 00:08:55,906
Rita Shelton.

120
00:08:55,981 --> 00:08:57,495
She's a nurse at Westside.

121
00:08:57,660 --> 00:08:58,760
So I got an alibi.

122
00:08:58,921 --> 00:09:02,304
Secondly, I've never even met Garza,
so you got no motive.

123
00:09:02,398 --> 00:09:03,890
How about murder-for-hire?

124
00:09:10,190 --> 00:09:12,072
I want my lawyer and a phone.

125
00:09:12,490 --> 00:09:15,098
After you're booked, like everyone else.

126
00:09:16,960 --> 00:09:18,820
Look into the camera, please.

127
00:09:21,494 --> 00:09:23,780
Thank you very much. You can step away.

128
00:09:28,420 --> 00:09:30,331
Hang on. That's my partner.

129
00:09:33,080 --> 00:09:34,480
- What's going on?
- I don't know.

130
00:09:34,500 --> 00:09:35,990
Your guess is as good as mine.

131
00:09:36,113 --> 00:09:38,220
I've got to get to my brother!

132
00:09:40,695 --> 00:09:42,235
They put me on leave.

133
00:09:42,481 --> 00:09:43,516
So before you go telling

134
00:09:43,610 --> 00:09:45,808
- certain people things you think...
- Andrea, hello?

135
00:09:45,840 --> 00:09:49,580
Fingerprints, mug shot...
I'm a little busy right now.

136
00:09:49,640 --> 00:09:51,180
Let's go, detective.

137
00:09:52,940 --> 00:09:54,260
You are a lucky man, Hopper.

138
00:09:54,270 --> 00:09:57,231
I got you one of the best defense
attorneys in the state: Barry Colburn.

139
00:09:57,262 --> 00:09:59,048
<i>He'll meet you at the court
for arraignment.</i>

140
00:09:59,049 --> 00:10:00,966
Come on, Baxter.
You gotta do better than that.

141
00:10:00,967 --> 00:10:03,087
Now flex some federal muscle
<i>and get me outta here.</i>

142
00:10:03,134 --> 00:10:04,716
Doing my best. I've called all morning.

143
00:10:04,763 --> 00:10:07,162
Nobody's giving an inch,
not the D.A.'S office, not L.A.P.D.

144
00:10:07,200 --> 00:10:09,834
I'm a cop with a clean record
and an alibi.

145
00:10:10,040 --> 00:10:12,081
- How is this happening?
<i>- I know you're pissed.</i>

146
00:10:12,119 --> 00:10:13,943
But this hurts me, too.
Damien is on the run,

147
00:10:14,103 --> 00:10:16,942
and you're the only one he trusts.
This case hinges on his testimony.

148
00:10:17,008 --> 00:10:18,952
<i>Well, I'm</i> sorry
for being so insensitive.

149
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:21,590
Seriously, how am I supposed to find
my star witness without you?

150
00:10:21,618 --> 00:10:25,190
Did you see Damien last night?
<i>Did you talk to him? Give me something.</i>

151
00:10:27,710 --> 00:10:30,240
He left a message on my machine.
He wants me <i>to come get him.</i>

152
00:10:30,250 --> 00:10:32,293
Where is he?
What happened at the safe house?

153
00:10:32,369 --> 00:10:34,854
Focus, Baxter. I'm the one in jail.

154
00:10:35,232 --> 00:10:38,240
Now I can't help you or Damien
unless you get me outta here.

155
00:10:47,478 --> 00:10:48,560
Let's go.

156
00:10:48,640 --> 00:10:50,470
Hopper, why did you kill Garza?

157
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:06,819
Baxter tried to put in a good word
for you with the L.A. County D.A

158
00:11:06,951 --> 00:11:08,301
but Garza was one of theirs.

159
00:11:08,377 --> 00:11:10,071
- Right, Colburn...
- Barry.

160
00:11:10,609 --> 00:11:11,630
Where's Rita?

161
00:11:13,150 --> 00:11:14,238
We can't find her.

162
00:11:14,940 --> 00:11:16,879
What do you mean?
Did you check the hospital?

163
00:11:16,946 --> 00:11:19,112
She's not at the hospital,
she's not in her apartment,

164
00:11:19,113 --> 00:11:20,760
she's not answering her cell.

165
00:11:20,827 --> 00:11:23,302
The cops and my people
are looking for her.

166
00:11:23,359 --> 00:11:27,004
Colburn, your first
and last priority as of right now

167
00:11:27,108 --> 00:11:30,280
is to find Rita Shelton.
Do you understand me?

168
00:11:31,471 --> 00:11:32,472
Okay.

169
00:11:35,547 --> 00:11:36,652
By the way,

170
00:11:36,845 --> 00:11:40,030
pulled in a couple of favors
and got you some time with your sister.

171
00:11:40,596 --> 00:11:41,862
Jen, where is she?

172
00:11:42,826 --> 00:11:44,546
I'll see you in there, Hopper.

173
00:11:45,410 --> 00:11:49,040
- Oh, my God. Are you okay?
- Yeah, I'm gonna be fine. I'm fine.

174
00:11:49,196 --> 00:11:50,463
They said they found a gun.

175
00:11:50,548 --> 00:11:52,812
No. Well, they did.
Someone else put it there.

176
00:11:52,850 --> 00:11:54,248
- Who would put...
- I don't know.

177
00:11:54,314 --> 00:11:56,248
It doesn't matter
because I have an alibi.

178
00:11:56,872 --> 00:11:57,893
Rita Shelton.

179
00:11:59,020 --> 00:12:01,289
Wait, you and Rita, as in Chad's wife?

180
00:12:01,412 --> 00:12:02,914
Well, ex-wife, but...

181
00:12:04,820 --> 00:12:06,213
And you didn't tell me.

182
00:12:06,354 --> 00:12:08,870
Jen, we haven't been talking
as much as we... never mind that!

183
00:12:08,880 --> 00:12:11,006
I wanna know about those 6 hang ups
from last night.

184
00:12:11,044 --> 00:12:13,090
And don't give me that mess
about the phones.

185
00:12:13,137 --> 00:12:14,080
It's nothing, really.

186
00:12:14,090 --> 00:12:15,917
Is everything okay
between you and Randall?

187
00:12:15,936 --> 00:12:17,374
- Of course.
- Jen, I...

188
00:12:33,110 --> 00:12:34,240
I'm gonna kill him.

189
00:12:34,336 --> 00:12:36,009
Who you killing now?

190
00:12:36,890 --> 00:12:38,026
Chad.

191
00:12:38,772 --> 00:12:39,868
Jennifer.

192
00:12:40,378 --> 00:12:41,465
You're lookin' well.

193
00:12:42,440 --> 00:12:43,470
Come on, partner.

194
00:12:44,000 --> 00:12:45,340
Time to face the music.

195
00:12:47,656 --> 00:12:49,795
Boy, you know,
cops will pull a lot of crazy stunts

196
00:12:49,831 --> 00:12:52,013
to weasel out of a meeting
with Internal Affairs.

197
00:12:52,245 --> 00:12:55,457
But committing a murder, that definitely
wins a prize, right, Hopper?

198
00:12:55,779 --> 00:12:58,158
You have an ugly smile.
People say that about you,

199
00:12:58,332 --> 00:12:59,834
especially women.

200
00:13:01,500 --> 00:13:03,659
We'll meet you up on four, guys.

201
00:13:03,881 --> 00:13:06,740
I need a little quality time
with my old partner here.

202
00:13:07,703 --> 00:13:09,724
I said we'll you up on four.

203
00:13:11,443 --> 00:13:12,454
Come on.

204
00:13:20,330 --> 00:13:22,550
You get the score of the Dodgers game?

205
00:13:26,768 --> 00:13:28,932
I know Andrea is a dirty cop.
You'll help me prove it.

206
00:13:28,983 --> 00:13:31,451
Yeah, I got a few other things
on my mind right now besides

207
00:13:31,491 --> 00:13:33,988
what my partner may or may not be into.

208
00:13:34,017 --> 00:13:36,453
Yeah, this whole
murdering-the-assistant-D.A thing,

209
00:13:36,484 --> 00:13:37,636
it's a real shame, isn't it?

210
00:13:37,656 --> 00:13:40,021
You know this thing screams setup
from like a mile away.

211
00:13:40,040 --> 00:13:42,200
Setup? No, they got you cold, man.

212
00:13:42,295 --> 00:13:43,751
Weapon, prints...

213
00:13:44,534 --> 00:13:46,590
But you got an alibi, right? Rita...

214
00:13:47,719 --> 00:13:50,125
Been spending a lot of time
with her lately.

215
00:13:50,792 --> 00:13:54,007
When you gonna make an honest woman
of her, get married already?

216
00:13:54,413 --> 00:13:57,550
Tell the truth. It bugs you
she kept my last name, doesn't it?

217
00:13:58,477 --> 00:14:00,590
You need a breath mint.

218
00:14:03,050 --> 00:14:04,820
Here's what I don't understand...

219
00:14:05,300 --> 00:14:07,090
You don't want to break
some unspoken code

220
00:14:07,109 --> 00:14:08,179
by telling on your partner,

221
00:14:08,198 --> 00:14:10,448
yet you got no problem sleeping
with another man's wife?

222
00:14:10,478 --> 00:14:13,016
You were divorced,
and we weren't partners anymore.

223
00:14:13,046 --> 00:14:15,370
You expect me to believe
those years we rolled togeth...

224
00:14:15,380 --> 00:14:18,206
It never happened, Chad... Never.

225
00:14:23,891 --> 00:14:26,720
How is she these days, my little Rita?

226
00:14:28,030 --> 00:14:29,391
It's been a while, but there's

227
00:14:29,432 --> 00:14:32,616
certain things you just never forget.
You know, like in the shower...

228
00:14:35,830 --> 00:14:37,650
You better watch it, convict.

229
00:14:38,519 --> 00:14:40,610
You play this right, I can help you.

230
00:14:41,460 --> 00:14:43,330
But you screw with me...

231
00:14:52,328 --> 00:14:53,440
Shelton!

232
00:14:56,776 --> 00:14:59,690
Why do I get the feeling
you know more than you're telling?

233
00:14:59,940 --> 00:15:01,196
'Cause I do.

234
00:15:04,189 --> 00:15:06,777
And due to the severity of the crime
and the physical evidences

235
00:15:06,797 --> 00:15:09,824
against the suspect,
the county requests no bail. We ask...

236
00:15:09,854 --> 00:15:11,543
Your Honor,
the district attorney's office

237
00:15:11,593 --> 00:15:14,267
has been made aware
of an exculpatory witness

238
00:15:14,298 --> 00:15:17,017
- who can attest to my client's...
- A witness that we can't locate

239
00:15:17,037 --> 00:15:18,022
at this time, Your Honor.

240
00:15:18,053 --> 00:15:20,397
We consider the suspect
to be a danger and a flight risk.

241
00:15:20,418 --> 00:15:21,673
- Can we ask...
- Flight risk?

242
00:15:21,731 --> 00:15:24,330
He's a decorated 12-year veteran
of the department.

243
00:15:24,380 --> 00:15:28,005
Veteran or not, the People are pursuing
a charge of first-degree murder.

244
00:15:28,157 --> 00:15:30,439
Very well. People's request is granted.

245
00:15:30,621 --> 00:15:33,644
Suspect will be held without bail
